@node editorial "Editorial" 

@{FG Shine}Welcome to AmiChannel News@{FG Text}

Hello and welcome to the 0 issue of @{B}AmiChannel News@{UB}

What is @{B}AmiChannel News@{UB}? It is an electronic magazine dedicated to our favourite
platform, @{B}Amiga@{UB}. @{I}"Oh no, another e-mag!" @{UI}, you'll exclaim. No, not another. This
is  the  magazine ONE. It is true that exists a few of them and some of them are
sincerely  good, but this one is mainly oriented to News, and the other you know
are lacking of this.

@{B}AmiChannel  News@{UB}  was born by an idea of @{I}Victor Garcia Valero @{UI}, co-publishing of
the best e-Mag in spanish (and the only one!) called @{B}Amiga Channel@{UB} and therefore
we can consider this one as the big sister of the one you're reading. In fact, I
hope in the next issues of this magazine we could include some selected articles
from  @{B}Amiga Channel@{UB}. To do this I can count with the invaluable collaboration of
@{I}Alvaro  Morales @{UI} ( alias  @{I}Newton @{UI})  who  makes  the translations of the texts in
spanish to english. Without him, this magazine couldn't exist (thanks man!)

This  magazine  has  born  not only to serve to the @{B}Amiga@{UB} Community all over the
world, but also we wish to make notice about the existence of @{B}Amiga@{UB} in Spain and
Sud-America, after all '@{B}Amiga@{UB}' is a spanish word.

This  effort is a small part of the effort which is making @{B}S.A.U.@{UB} (@{B}Spanish Amiga
Users@{UB}),  to  help to keep and expand the @{B}Amiga@{UB} market. Our fundamental objective
is  to  support  to  the  spanish-speaking  community, but we also think that is
necessary  to  contribute  to  this hard work. For this sake, @{B}S.A.U.@{UB} keeps a Web
site  where  you'll  be  able to find last hour news about @{B}Amiga@{UB} World. The main
web of @{B}S.A.U.@{UB} can be found here:

	@{B}http://www.arrakis.es/amiga/@{UB}                (Spain)

and it keeps four mirrors:

	@{B}http://club.idecnet.com/~dragon/sau/@{UB}        (Spain)
	@{B}http://soporte.databasedm.es/amiga/sau/@{UB}     (Spain)
	@{B}http://www.isocanda.org/per/sau/@{UB}            (Academic Net)
	@{B}http://www.larevisteria.com/sau/@{UB}            (California, USA)

Don't doubt to visit us. You won't be sorry.

Finally,  to  be  the  first issue is more than enough. We let you with the news
which have happened during April.

Greetings.

