@node not1 "U.S. WEST COAST AMIGA SHOW AMIWEST98 ANNOUNCED."

@{FG Shine}U.S. WEST COAST @{B}AMIGA@{UB} SHOW @{B}AMIWEST98@{UB} ANNOUNCED@{FG Text}
----------------------------------------------

@{FG Fill}DATE: 1998/04/01@{FG Text}

@{I}PRESS RELEASE - FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE @{UI}

We are proud to announce The @{B}Amiga@{UB} West Coast show, @{B}AmiWest98@{UB}.

Join us at the Ramada Inn in Sacramento, California on July 11th and 12th, 1998.
This showcase of @{B}Amiga@{UB} talent is being jointly sponsored by the @{B}Sacramento Amiga
Computer  Club@{UB},  the @{B}Redwood Empire Amiga Users Group@{UB}, and other West Coast user
groups and is officially sanctioned by @{B}Amiga, Inc.@{UB} and the @{B}Industry Council Open
Amiga@{UB} (@{B}ICOA@{UB}).

@{B}AmiWest98@{UB}  is the first @{B}Amiga@{UB} show to be produced on the West Coast in over four
years. We expect attendance from all over the Western United States with special
guests from throughout the world. Come see the newest in @{B}Amiga@{UB} improvements; see
and  speak  with the developers during two full days of show exhibits from major
@{B}Amiga@{UB} companies.

@{B}ICOA@{UB},  the official developer arm for the @{B}Amiga@{UB}, will also be hosting a four day
Developer's  Conference  at  the show. The main events will be held on July 11th
and  12th  with  seminars  and developer sessions spanning the four days between
Friday, July 10th and Monday, July 13th.

Space  is available for rent to companies, clubs, organizations, and individuals
producing  @{B}Amiga@{UB} related products and services. This four day weekend event will
showcase the progress that IS the @{B}Amiga@{UB} Community.

Booth pricing is available on our web page: @{B}http://www.sacc.org/amiwest/@{UB}

Admission to the event is as follows:
     $8 (One day Pass - Paid by July 1, 1998)
    $10 (One day Pass - Paid at the door)

    $12 (Two day pass - Paid by July 1, 1998)
    $15 (Two day pass - Paid at the door)

There  will also be a banquet on Saturday evening, July 11th, with guest speaker
to  be announced. Banquet tickets are $25 per plate and MUST be paid in advance.
Seating  is  limited  and tickets for the banquet are available on a first come,
first served basis.

For  more information contact either @{I}Alan Crandall @{UI}at @{I}alanwall@sonic.net @{UI}or @{I}John
Zacharias @{UI}at @{I}jzachar@calweb.com @{UI}or write to us at:

@{B}AmiWest98@{UB}
c/o @{B}Sacramento Amiga Computer Club@{UB}
P.O. Box 19784
Sacramento, CA 95819-0784

Come visit us at our web site!

@{I}Alan Crandall @{UI}
@{I}alanwall@sonic.net @{UI}

@{I}John Zacharias @{UI}
@{I}jzachar@calweb.com @{UI}

"1998 is going to be a fun ride!" @{B}AmiWest98@{UB}, get in, strap in, hang on!

