@node not9 "MYSTIQUE ANNOUNCES CREATION OF NEW FOLDER ON AMINETJUST FOR CHILDREN."

@{FG Shine}@{B}MYSTIQUE@{UB} ANNOUNCES CREATION OF NEW FOLDER ON @{B}AMINET@{UB} JUST FOR CHILDREN@{FG Text}
--------------------------------------------------------------------

@{FG Fill}DATE: 1998/04/07@{FG Text}

@{I}FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE @{UI}

As  hosts of the @{B}Amiga@{UB}'s Premier Children's Site, it brings us great pleasure to
announce  the  completion  of  Stage  Two  of  our  @{B}Made  For  KiDS@{UB} campaign for
Children's Software on the @{B}Amiga@{UB}.

We  have  overseen  the  creation  of  a  new  folder  on  the @{B}Aminet@{UB} solely for
children's  software and have introduced a brand new Kids' Software Directory on
our site.

This  new  directory  is  divided into several different categories and has been
carefully designed to provide you with the information you want with the maximum
of ease and minimum of fuss.

It really is the best way to find software for your children on the internet!

Features of the directory:

 * Comprehensive  Reviews:  Read  a  quality review of a title before taking the
   time to download it!
 * Screenshots
 * System Compatibility Information

 * RAM Requirements
 * Graphics Modes Supported
 * @{B}Workbench@{UB} Versions Supported
 * CPUs Supported
 * Languages Supported (Default is English)

 * Age  Ranges:  Don't  waste  time downloading software that's too easy/hard to
   use!
 * Local  Downloads:  Covering  the  entire  planet,  courtesy of the incredible
   @{B}Aminet@{UB} archives!

We believe this new format to be a great enhancement over the @{B}Aminet@{UB}'s format as
it is specifically designed to help you get the best, most suitable software for
your children.

The creation of this directory has taken a considerable amount of time and shows
our commitment to children's software on the @{B}Amiga@{UB}.

Check out our website for even more pages for kids including:

 * Web  Forum: Make your voice heard on the future of children's software on the
   @{B}Amiga@{UB}.
 * Original Stories: For children to read online or download to read later!
 * @{B}Made  For KiDS@{UB}: Full details of the @{B}Made For KiDS@{UB} campaign including its aims
   and objectives and details about how you can help!

We  would  like to thank @{I}Urban Mueller @{UI}for his support and work in creating this
new folder.

@{I}Urban, @{UI}we couldn't have done it without you - keep up the great work!

We  would  also like to express our thanks to @{B}Haage&Partner@{UB} who have shown their
support  for  our  projects  by  generously  sponsoring  us  of  a copy of their
excellent @{B}StormC@{UB} software to aid our developments.

This, in conjunction with the sponsorship of our company by @{B}Amiga International@{UB},
shows  the  overwhelming  support for Mystique and for our efforts to ensure the
future of the @{B}Amiga@{UB} as a computer of choice for children and education.

Finally, we would also like to announce the opening of the new @{B}CP@{UB} Support Site.

Here you will find information about, screenshots, reviews and downloads of @{B}CP@{UB} -
the  @{B}Amiga@{UB}'s Premier Children's Software. Surely a section of the site you can't
afford to miss!

We  would  be very grateful if you could please complete our short Survey on the
future  specs  of  @{B}CP@{UB}, so that we may identify the base configuration for @{B}CP@{UB} and
better serve your child's computing needs!

All the best...

