@node not11 "AMICON ANNOUNCES THE 3RD ANNUAL MIDWEST AMIGA EXPOSITION."

@{FG Shine}@{B}AMICON@{UB} ANNOUNCES THE 3RD ANNUAL @{B}MIDWEST AMIGA EXPOSITION@{UB}@{FG Text}
--------------------------------------------------------

@{FG Fill}DATE: 1998/04/14@{FG Text}

@{B}AmiCON@{UB} -  The  @{B}Amiga  Central  Ohio Network@{UB}  is proud to announce The 3rd Annual
@{B}Midwest  Amiga  Exposition@{UB}!  We  are  excited to bring this dynamic event to the
Amiga community, and we want you to be a part of it!

Where:
Hyatt Regency
350 North High Street
Columbus, OH. 43215
(614) 463-1234

When:
October 2nd, 3rd, and 4th.

With the continued success of the @{B}Midwest Amiga Exposition@{UB} we are able to expand
and grow to serve the Amiga community better than ever before! The @{B}Midwest Amiga
Exposition@{UB} was created for users by users in order to bring the community closer
together.  See  and  test  drive  the  newest,  most exciting @{B}Amiga@{UB} products and
systems  available!  Attend  informational  classes  and  seminars, and meet the
people  who  support  and develop for the @{B}Amiga@{UB}. Everything @{B}Amiga@{UB} under one roof
for three days straight!

This  year  we  have  expanded the floor space to almost 7,000 square feet. More
than  double  the  size of last years show! Exhibitors can now rent space by the
square  foot  with  several  size  booths available: 6x5, 8x5, 13x11, 16x11, and
20x20.  Six  foot display tables with tablecloth and skirting are furnished with
rental  space  for no extra charge. For those exhibitors who want a professional
look, pipe and drape is also available for rental on a per foot basis.

Along  with  many  @{B}Amiga@{UB}  notables  and guest speakers, we will also have hourly
prize  raffles,  games,  contests,  and  a  GRAND PRIZE drawing to highlight the
event!

Seminars  and  classes  are becoming an integral part of any serious @{B}Amiga@{UB} show.
Vendors  and  developers  are  anxious to present new and updated products to an
eager  community. We are committed to bringing top quality seminars to the @{B}Amiga@{UB}
community in order for you, the end user, to get the most out of your @{B}Amiga@{UB}.

To  better  serve show attendees, single day and two-day tickets for the @{B}Midwest
Amiga  Exposition@{UB} will be available this year. And, don't worry about rushing to
buy  tickets  ahead  of  time,  all tickets will be available at the door to the
show, thus eliminating any possible problems with "tickets lost in the mail".

On  Friday,  October 2nd developers from all over the world can meet to find out
the  latest  in @{B}Amiga@{UB} affairs. Classes and seminars will also be offered on that
day as well.

Saturday,  October  3rd,  and  Sunday,  October 4th, the show floor will be open
along  with seminars and classes. Hourly prize raffles, games (with prizes!) and
just about every company that sells something for the @{B}Amiga@{UB} will be there.

@{I}About the Hyatt Regency: @{UI}

The  Hyatt  Regency  Columbus hotel at the Greater Columbus Convention Center is
the  setting  for the 1998 @{B}Midwest Amiga Exposition@{UB}. Superb downtown location is
just minutes away from Columbus International Airport and allows for easy access
for  both  guests  and  exhibitors. This hotel features many amenities including
indoor  swimming  pool,  airport shuttle, currency exchange, safe deposit boxes,
covered parking, and room service all at an exceptional value.

Mention  our show to the Hyatt when you call to reserve and you are eligible for
a special @{B}Midwest Amiga Exposition@{UB} discount rate!

General  Admission Tickets: $8.00  for  a  one-day pass (good either Saturday or
Sunday), $12.00 both days.Some seminars may be extra.

The @{B}Amiga@{UB} needs a presence, and it also needs dedicated people working in unison
to  help  promote  what  we  think  is  simply  the best home computer available
yesterday,  today and tomorrow! Shows like ours help potential and current users
find  out what is available, how they can get it, and where the @{B}Amiga@{UB} is headed.
Join  us,  this  year, at the @{B}1998 Midwest Amiga Exposition@{UB}, as we celebrate the
machine and the people that make it all possible!

Look  for  our  ads in all major U.S. @{B}Amiga@{UB} publications, and our banner on your
favorite web sites, coming soon!

Visit   @{B}http://www.amicon.org/mae.html@{UB}   for   more  information  and  exhibitor
registration.

Email: @{I}Dave Pearce @{UI}- @{I}dpearce@infinet.com @{UI}

