@node not18 "SYZYGY'S DIGITAL UNIVERSE V1.03 AVAILABLE ON CD-ROM FOR HALF PRICE."

@{FG Shine}SYZYGY'S DIGITAL UNIVERSE V1.03 AVAILABLE ON CD-ROM FOR HALF PRICE@{FG Text}
------------------------------------------------------------------

@{FG Fill}DATE: 1998/04/24@{FG Text}

@{I}OFFICIAL RELEASE ANNOUNCEMENT 980419 @{UI}

- @{I}What is The @{B}Digital Universe @{UB}? @{UI}

The  @{B}Digital Universe@{UB} is an award-winning astronomical simulator package for the
@{B}Amiga@{UB}  computer.  Since release, it has become the standard software package for
the amateur and professional astronomer. With our new lower price, we expect the
software  to  become  more accessible to the casual astronomy enthusiast, and to
those interested in generally learning more about astronomy.

For  more  information on the capabilities of @{B}The Digital Universe@{UB}, please refer
to @{B}http://www.syz.com/DU/amigacd.html@{UB} on the web.

- @{I}The New CD-ROM Distribution @{UI}

The  original  distribution of @{B}The Digital Universe@{UB} consisted of 14 floppy disks
and  a  printed  user  manual, all enclosed within a binder. Since more and more
@{B}Amiga@{UB}  owners  now have CD-ROM drives, we have decided that a CD distribution of
@{B}The  Digital  Universe@{UB} is now more practical than it would have been a few years
ago.

In   addition,  the  entire  printed  user  manual  is  available  online  as  a
context-sensitive  help  system.  We had many comments from individuals who said
that  with  the online help and the general user-friendly nature of the package,
they have never needed to consult the printed manual.

With  these factors in mind, and to keep costs down, the new CD-ROM distribution
consists  of  single shrink wrapped CD-R, with no printed documentation, box, or
user  manual.  Online  documentation  is  provided to explain how to install the
software,  start  the program, and access the online help. For most people, this
is all that is required.

The  software  and  databases  included  on  the  CD are the complete functional
version  of  @{B}Digital  Universe V1.03@{UB} that was being shipped on floppy disk until
now. For this reason, existing owners of the original @{B}V1.03@{UB} distribution have no
reason to upgrade to the new CD distribution.

- @{I}Cost of the @{B}V1.03 @{UB}CD Version of @{B}Digital Universe @{UB}@{UI}

With  the  original  floppy-based  distribution  of  @{B}Digital  Universe@{UB}, we had a
complicated  price structure reflecting the widely varying costs of shipping the
package  around  the world. The new CD distribution is much smaller and lighter,
and  thus  shipping  charges  do not vary as much. Therefore, we are happy to be
able  to  offer  a  single price of $75 Canadian for the package, which includes
shipment via air mail to anywhere in the world.

The  lower  cost  of shipping means that international customers will be able to
obtain @{B}The Digital Universe@{UB} for even less than half of its original cost.

As a rough guideline, you can use the following table to estimate the equivalent
cost  in  your  own  currency.  The  amounts quoted below were obtained from the
interbank  rates  on  April  11,  1998 based on $75 Canadian, and will naturally
fluctuate:

United States:   52.62 USD
Germany:         95.84 DEM
UK:              31.44 GBP
France:         321.53 FRF
Switzerland:     79.62 CHF
Italy:        94860.00 ITL
Finland:        291.20 FIM
Sweden:         414.06 SEK
Australia:       79.82 AUD

Canadian  residents  must  add 7% GST. Keep in mind that your country may charge
duty or import taxes on software sent from Canada (some countries charge as high
as  25%),  which  would  be  payable  to  your country's customs office when the
package arrives.

- @{I}Bulk Orders @{UI}

If  a large group is interested in obtaining several copies of the software in a
single  order,  you  may be eligible for a "bulk order" rate of $65 Canadian per
copy (a discount of $10). The bulk rate will be given if either:

 * A group makes a single order of 5 copies or more, which are to be sent in one
   batch to a single address
 * A  group  makes  a  single order of 10 copies or more, whch are to be sent to
   individual addresses.

- @{I}What about a @{B}Version 2.0 @{UB} for the @{B}Amiga @{UB} ? @{UI}

Some  of  you  may  be  aware  of the decision-making process we have been going
through  as  to whether or not to develop a @{B}V2.0@{UB} of @{B}DU@{UB} for the @{B}Amiga@{UB}. So far, we
have  had  a rather encouraging response from our online survey available on the
web at @{B}http://www.syz.com/DU/amiga2.html@{UB} - if you haven't already filled it out,
we  encourage  you to do so. At any rate, we are planning on using a combination
of  the  results  from  this survey and the sales of this CDROM @{B}V1.03@{UB} to help us
decide whether or not to develop a @{B}V2.0@{UB}.

If  @{B}V2.0@{UB}  is developed, it will sell for our "regular" @{B}Digital Universe@{UB} price of
$150 Canadian.

- @{I}What about @{B}PPC @{UB} support? @{UI}

A  beta  version  of  a patch to allow the @{B}SAS/C@{UB} compiler to create code for @{B}PPC@{UB}
machines is currently available. In the next little while, we will be looking at
porting  @{B}The  Digital  Universe@{UB} to @{B}PPC@{UB}. If you own a @{B}PPC@{UB} board, are a registered
owner  of  @{B}Digital  Universe@{UB},  and  may  be  interested  in beta testing @{B}Digital
Universe V1.03@{UB} for the @{B}PPC@{UB}, please let us know. If the @{B}PPC@{UB} version is relatively
easy  to  complete,  we hope to offer it as a free upgrade (via email) to anyone
who purchased @{B}V1.03@{UB}, either on floppy or CDROM.

- @{I}If you already own the previous floppy-based @{B}Digital Universe V1.03 @{UB}, how are 
  you affected by this release? @{UI}

Since the software and data files of the CDROM distribution are exactly the same
as  what you already own, you have no reason to obtain the @{B}V1.03@{UB} CDROM yourself.
But  since  sales  of  this  CDROM  will  have a large impact on our decision of
whether  or not to develop @{B}V2.0@{UB}, you may want to encourage other @{B}Amiga@{UB} owners to
think about purchasing the CD. See @{I}"Referral Program" @{UI} below for more details.

- @{I}If  you  were  planning  on  waiting  for  a @{B}V2.0 @{UB}release of @{B}DU @{UB}, how are you 
  affected? @{UI}

If  you  are in this situation, you are the perfect candidate to obtain @{B}V1.03@{UB} on
CDROM  now.  Since  purchasing @{B}V1.03@{UB} on CD now will entitle you, as a registered
owner, to obtain future upgrades for half of the regular price, you will be able
to  obtain  @{B}V2.0@{UB} when and if released, for $75 (half of the planned $150 price).
The  net  result is that you pay the same amount to obtain @{B}V1.03@{UB} now and upgrade
to  @{B}V2.0@{UB}  later  as  you  would  to  buy @{B}V2.0@{UB} directly. Plus, you have the added
benefits of being able to use @{B}Digital Universe@{UB} now, as well as helping us obtain
the resources required to develop @{B}V2.0@{UB}.

- @{I}What  if  the  regular  cost  of @{B}DU @{UB} ($150) has always seemed a bit expensive 
  for you? @{UI}

If we develop @{B}V2.0@{UB} for the @{B}Amiga@{UB}, we would expect to sell it for $150 - the same
as  what  the  original  floppy-based  @{B}V1.03@{UB}  sold for. If you are only casually
interested  in  astronomy, and the $150 price seems a bit expensive, we strongly
encourage you to consider the purchase of the CDROM Version 1.03 now for $75. We
may  discontinue the CD-based @{B}V1.03@{UB} if a CD-based @{B}V2.0@{UB} is developed, and if this
happens, you will no longer be able to obtain @{B}Digital Universe@{UB} for $75.

- @{I}Referral Program @{UI}

In  an  effort  to  reward those @{B}Digital Universe@{UB} owners who help to promote our
software,  we'd  like  to announce our referral program. If you are a registered
owner   of   @{B}Digital  Universe@{UB},  tell  someone  about  our  software,  and  they
consequently  purchase  @{B}V1.03@{UB}  of  @{B}DU@{UB}  on  CDROM  from  us, we'll give you a $10
discount  on your upgrade to @{B}V2.0@{UB} if and when it is released. You can accumulate
discounts  for  each  referral  made,  up  to  the point at which you get a free
upgrade.  Note  that this must be a "personal" referral (ie: just linking to our
web  page won't count), and that the person ordering the package must provide us
with your name when letting us know where they heard about @{B}The Digital Universe@{UB}.

- @{I}How can you try out @{B}Digital Universe @{UB} first, before purchasing it? @{UI}

A   demo  version  of  @{B}The  Digital  Universe@{UB}  is  available  on  @{B}Aminet@{UB},  named
@{B}Dig_Universe.lha@{UB}  and located in the @{B}biz/demo@{UB} directory. It lets you try out all
the features of @{B}Digital Universe@{UB}, with the following restrictions:

 * only a small subset of the hypertext encyclopedia is included
 * it doesn't let you simulate the night sky's appearance after June 1, 1998
 * it only shows objects for a region of the sky in the vicinity of Orion.

Nevertheless,  it  should  give  you a good indication of whether or not @{B}Digital
Universe@{UB} is for you.

- @{I}How can you get a copy of @{B}V1.03 @{UB} on CDROM? @{UI}

If  you  would like to purchase a copy of @{B}Digital Universe@{UB}, you can do so either
directly  from  us  or  from  one  of our distributors. If you want to contact a
distributor,  let  us know your location and we'll be able to tell you who might
be  able  to get a copy to you the quickest. Keep in mind that all prices quoted
in  this  messages  are  our "suggested retail prices" and that distributors may
sell for more or less.

We  are also always on the lookout for new distributors of @{B}The Digital Universe@{UB}.
If  you think you may be interested in distributing our software in your region,
give  us  a rough estimate of the volume you might expect to deal with and we'll
send  you  out  more  information about our requirements of distributors and the
